[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is 3 138 115, with reports of cases by 214 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 97.4% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA, with over 1 million confirmed cases now represents 33.0% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 217 970 deaths have been reported, 213 337 (97.9%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Spain is number 2, and Italy is number 3, followed by France, the UK, Germany, Turkey, Russia, Iran, and China as number 10, with the UK surpassing Germany, and Russia surpassing Iran in the past 24 hours, in terms of cumulative case counts. - Mod.MPP]

