[Take away message: cruise ships are ideal incubators for easily transmitted diseases (which we have learned is where COVID-19 sits). When I was a CDC EIS (Epidemic Intelligence Service) officer, frequent outbreak investigations involved EIS officers boarding cruise ships for foodborne outbreaks -- usually armed with their own care packages of food and drinks. Most of those outbreaks were bacterial and bacterial toxin related. Then it morphed into predominantly viral norovirus related outbreaks (see Norovirus - USA: frozen raspberries, cruise ships, 2019 20200428.7278050) for good background of 2019 norovirus on cruise ships). And influenza related outbreaks were identified as well, probably helping to obfuscate the identification of the SARS-CoV-2 outbreaks in the early days on board the ships. There are definitely lessons to be learned here. - Mod.MPP]

